        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(vydra,xai,runway,pixverse,deepinfra,together,elevenlabs,microsoft): bound JSON response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nReplace unbounded `await response.json()` with `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB cap)\nacross 8 provider extensions (12 call sites in 12 files).\n\n## Changes\n\nModules: vydra, xai, deepinfra, pixverse, runway, together, elevenlabs,\nmicrosoft-foundry, microsoft. Each site uses a file-local constant. Added\n`vi.mock` bridge for test files with plain mock objects.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Real environment tested**: Real `node:http` server, real `fetch()`, real\n  `readResponseWithLimit`. Node v22.12.0.\n\n## Evidence\n### Real HTTP proof (against live server)\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_bounded_json.mts\n\n[proof] real server, cap=1048576 bytes, would-stream≈67108864 bytes\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error :: msg=\"Error: JSON response exceeds 1048576 bytes\"\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: server sent ≈ cap bytes, not ~64 MiB :: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly :: status=ok id=batch-1\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap :: buffered=33554457 bytes (> 1048576)\n\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\nThe proof harness starts a real `node:http` server with no Content-Length,\nstreams ~64 MiB of JSON, and verifies `readResponseWithLimit` cancels the\nstream at the 1 MiB cap. The negative control proves the cap is load-bearing.\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/deepinfra/video-generation-provider.test.ts extensions/pixverse/video-generation-provider.test.ts\n  Test Files  2 passed (2)\n       Tests  38 passed (38)\n```\n\n**Label**: security\n\n_AI-assisted._\n",
